{
  "root_cause": "Without SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE enabled, each CudaIpcTensorTransportProxy carries a per-item CUDA IPC handle instead of the shared pool handle. Under high concurrency the MmItemMemoryPool recycler can free and reuse a device memory chunk before the scheduler process opens the per-item handle, causing the receiver to dereference a stale (already recycled) device pointer and crash with HIP error: invalid device pointer.",
  "fix": "export SGLANG_USE_IPC_POOL_HANDLE_CACHE=1",
  "evidence": "[2026-07-16 12:50:59 TP1] Failed to deserialize from CUDA IPC handle (HIP error: invalid device pointer"
}
